<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="244" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d244">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hunter</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-17"><hi rend="italic">September 17,
                                    1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In name of Mrs. McKinley, President Roosevelt, and American Government
                            and people, please express through proper channel to President Estrada
                            sincere estimation of his messages of personal sympathy and of the
                            fraternal sentiment of Guatemala in this hour of affliction.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>